snippet: Egyptian prosecutors also announced charges against two Israeli citizens, who it said were agents of Mossad, Israel’s spy service.
abstract: Egyptian prosecutors say they have arrested two Egyptian citizens on charges of spying for Israel, saying suspects confessed to supplying Israeli agents with information on Egypt’s military and its political movements; also charge two Israeli citizens for being officers of Mossad.
lead_paragraph: Egyptian prosecutors also announced charges against two Israeli citizens, who it said were agents of Mossad, Israel’s spy service.

headline.main: 2 Egyptians Charged With Spying for Israel
headline.print_headline: Egypt: 4 Charged as Spies for Israel
